  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-bpa-retrying-a-process-instance-does-not-trigger-the-actions/qaq-p/13743018</id>
    <title>SAP BPA - Retrying a process instance does not trigger the actions</title>
    <updated>2024-06-26T10:59:38.441000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>KDYA</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/179196</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi all,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;I've done an interesting observation the past week on the Build Process Automation monitoring tool - especially the 'Retry' functionality.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;When retrying a process instance containing an action then the action is not execute instantly. Below are screen shots from an instance where a process is retried after action failure. But upon retrying the instance the action is not triggered - at least not within the first hour.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="KDYA_0-1719388745303.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/128827i06199211DD843828/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="KDYA_0-1719388745303.png" alt="KDYA_0-1719388745303.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Below is another example on a process instance that was retried - Six hours later the action was triggered.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="KDYA_1-1719389439112.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/128829i253000C81453BC49/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="KDYA_1-1719389439112.png" alt="KDYA_1-1719389439112.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Above logs are on the same process - but two different instances. The first step of the process is an action - so we are not pending multiple steps before executing the action. When no action failure occurs then the process instance is executed within seconds.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The issue seems to only to occur upon retrying a process instance.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Has anyone done the same observations on the retry functionality?&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/sap-bpa-retrying-a-process-instance-does-not-trigger-the-actions/qaq-p/13743018"/>
    <published>2024-06-26T10:59:38.441000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
