    <title>Process automation Integration with microsoft graph</title>
    <updated>2024-06-28T09:55:21.776000+02:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>tirthankar_chakraborty</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/214661</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;Hi Experts,&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;We are trying to integrate microsoft share point with SAP process automation. We had followed the guidelines as given in the documentation:&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/sharepoint?view=graph-rest-1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/graph/api/resources/sharepoint?view=graph-rest-1.0&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_0-1719560871716.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/129949iA9515B177A9C8951/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="tirthankar_chakraborty_0-1719560871716.png" alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_0-1719560871716.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;For accessing Applications and relevant configurations and authorisation are set up in Azure including scope. Scope is added as per Microsoft documentation and the process works well from postman.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;While trying to call the same via actions, Scope is added to additional properties of destination along with other properties required to be called in Actions.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_1-1719561030179.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/129951i241FA5E36CD1F661/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="tirthankar_chakraborty_1-1719561030179.png" alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_1-1719561030179.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;A custom Action is created with variable as site where sitename is to be entered and domain as below:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Destination path:&amp;nbsp;&lt;A href="https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow noreferrer"&gt;https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0&lt;/A&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Custom action end point:&amp;nbsp;&lt;SPAN class=""&gt;/sites/{domain}:/sites/{site}&lt;/SPAN&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;span class="lia-inline-image-display-wrapper lia-image-align-inline" image-alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_2-1719561120096.png" style="width: 400px;"&gt;&lt;img src="https://community.sap.com/t5/image/serverpage/image-id/129952i8D8ADF1746137F47/image-size/medium?v=v2&amp;amp;px=400" role="button" title="tirthankar_chakraborty_2-1719561120096.png" alt="tirthankar_chakraborty_2-1719561120096.png" /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;However, while testing the action, it gives http 200 but it does not retrive any value.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;The same however works from postman. We tried microsoft 365 SDK but it didnot work and hence we shifted to this method. Can anyone please suggest on this or if anyone has faced this issue before.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1452727"&gt;@SAPSupport1&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href="https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/15812"&gt;@Archana&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Thanks&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;Tirthankar&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;</content>
    <link href="https://community.sap.com/t5/technology-q-a/process-automation-integration-with-microsoft-graph/qaq-p/13745473"/>
    <published>2024-06-28T09:55:21.776000+02:00</published>
  </entry>
